Limits and Limitations for Trending Data in Analytics

Trended datasets count toward the overall CRM Analytics platform limits. To prevent performance degradation, certain limitations are placed on snapshot size and the number of trended datasets each user can create.

Check out the following limits on trending data:

* Maximum number of trended datasets per user: 5
* Maximum number of rows per snapshot: 100,000
* Maximum number of rows in the report to be trended: 500,000 for admins, 100,000 for non-admins
* Maximum total number of rows in a trended dataset: 5,000,000
* Maximum monthly number of rows for all snapshots per org: 40 million

To control the impact that trended datasets have on general org-wide limits, configure these limits:

* Max number of rows per snapshot
* Max total number of rows in a trended dataset
* Enable automatic deletion of inactive datasets

The best candidates for trending are reports that can be visualized in time and have some frequently changing values. Examples include open opportunities pipeline or escalated cases.

Some situations can prevent a report from successfully capturing data, including Jobs involving the User object, site switching, and instance maintenance.

Only the user who starts trending a report can stop it, but they can share the trending dashboard with other users. If another user wants to trend the same report, they must create a new trend.

After trending begins, do not change access rights or add/delete dimensions and measures. Changing the report or access rights can cause errors or inaccuracies at snapshot time.

If you modify a field in a report that is trended, the change is reflected in the associated dashboard from the time of the change onward.

Snapshots are taken every Sunday at midnight (local time), unless a different schedule is set when trending a report. Processing and surfacing the data requires more time, which can delay snapshots.

Trended datasets are created in their own private folders. You can move them to public folders using the Update Dataset button.

The dataflow that creates a trended dataset is auto-generated and cannot be viewed or modified. This restriction is required because the underlying trending logic can be sensitive to changes in the dataflow.
title: Limits and Limitations of Trending Data in Salesforce Analytics
